<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 6:58PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Talbot
County through 730 PM EDT...
At 658 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Talbotton, moving
northwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Talbotton, Junction City, Geneva, Olive Branch, Po Biddy Crossroads
and Baldwinville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
